      <h1 class='title'>Hong Kong: Sino-British Joint Declaration</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 March 2005 vol 670 c21WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_21ws' title='Col. 21WS &mdash; HL Deb 17 March 2005 vol 670 c21WS' name='column_21ws' href='#column_21ws' rel='bookmark'>21WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0670P0-06171'>
        <a name='S5LV0670P0_20050317_LWS_18'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-elizabeth-symons' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0670P0_20050317_LWS_18' title='Link to this speech by Ms Elizabeth Symons' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-elizabeth-symons" title="Ms Elizabeth Symons">The Minister of State, Foreign and Commonwealth Office (Baroness Symons of Vernham Dean)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0670P0-06171">The latest report on the implementation of the Sino-British Joint Declaration on Hong Kong (Cm 6484) was laid before the House today and copies have been placed in the Library of the House. A copy of the report is also available on the Foreign and Commonwealth Office website at<span class="italic">www.fco.gov.uk.</span> The report covers the period from 1 July to 31 December 2004 and includes a foreword by my right honourable friend the Foreign Secretary. I commend the report to the House.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
